      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:8:30:11",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) إِيَّاكَ وَ نُصُولَ الْخِضَابِ فَإِنَّ ذَلِكَ بُؤْسٌ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Abu Abdullah, from Muhammad Bin Ismail, from Muhammad Bin Uzafar, from umar Bin Yazeed who said, ",
          "‘Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘Beware of the discolouration of the dyeing, for in that is despair’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "11. A number of our people have narrated from Ahmad ibn abu ‘Abd Allah from Muhammad ibn ’Isma‘il from Muhammad ibn ‘Adhafir from ‘Umar ibn Yazid who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘You must not allow the hair dye to wear off because it is despair.’” "
        ]
      }
